The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Pak stadium

Karachi: Pakistani authorities are planning a new stadium in Islamabad to host matches at the 2008 Champions Trophy and 2011 World Cup. 

We are acquiring land in Islamabad and will sign a memorandum of understanding soon, said Saleem Altaf, PCBs director, cricket operations. We are hoping the new stadium will be ready before the Champions Trophy. 

The 2011 World Cup will be co-hosted by Pakistan, India, Sri Lanka and Bangladesh. 

 (REUTERS) 




